body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for reaching out to DataDrive Support. My name is Aaron Alexander. May I know your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Heather. Can you please verify your date of birth by sharing the day, month, and year as three six two zero one nine eight zero?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's three six March, two zero one nine.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you. Could you also provide the first four digits of your phone number as five six eight nine?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, it's five six eight nine.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for sharing that. We will look into your data management concern related to the Car Dealership. Is there anything specific you would like us to address?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, I'm just relieved that the issue is being taken care of.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: We understand the importance of your data security. Thank you for providing the necessary information, Heather. If you have any more questions or concerns, feel free to reach out. Have a great day!
